    <stitle>AIR COMPRESSOR: MIDLAND MODELS EL-1300 AND EL-1600 - DISASSEMBLE - PISTON AND CONNECTING ROD</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>PISTON AND CONNECTING ROD</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn crankshaft so that one connecting rod is at bottom of stroke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401109">Figure 9</hotlnk>). Remove connecting rod, bolts and bearing cap using a
                12-point 5/16 in. socket.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0401109" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0401109" filename="../figg04/G0401109.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Connecting Rod at Bottom of Stroke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove piston and rod assembly from cylinder block. Using a small hammer handle or a
                suitable piece of wood placed on the connecting rod, push rod and piston assembly out through the top of
                the block.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <para>Repeat steps 1 and 2 for the other rod/piston assembly.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After connecting rod and piston assembly have been removed, temporarily install bearing cap
                on connecting rod from which cap was removed by loosely installing rod bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove piston pin snap rings from piston assembly and press piston pin out of piston and
                connecting rod. Then remove compression and oil rings from piston using conventional piston ring
                expander. Use this procedure for both piston assemblies. Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401110">Figure 10</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401111">Figure 11</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0401110" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0401110" filename="../figg04/G0401110.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Piston and Connecting Rod</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.PISTON PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.PISTON</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.COMPRESSION RINGS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.SNAP RING</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.OIL RAIL EXPANDER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6.CONNECTING ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>7.OIL RAILS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0401111" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0401111" filename="../figg04/G0401111.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Removal of Compression Oil Rings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
